Why dual licensing?
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
A specification and its reference implementation serve different
purposes. The specification benefits from a documentation-style
license (CC BY 4.0) that emphasises attribution; the reference code
benefits from a software-style license (Apache-2.0) that grants
explicit patent rights and is universally accepted by both open and
closed downstreams.

This is the same pattern used by, for example, OpenAPI Initiative
(spec under MIT/CC BY, tooling under Apache-2.0) and the CNCF
landscape.

